The remove will remove it from the available list of SOC USB ports.Â  The free will just make sure the memory allocated for the SOC USB port is freed.
>> +
>> +	static void q6usb_component_remove(struct snd_soc_component *component)
>> +	{
>> +		...
> [1]
>
>> +		snd_soc_usb_remove_port(data->usb);
>> +		snd_soc_usb_free_port(data->usb);
